  'Use base-ten blocks: adding one rod increases the tens digit by 1.',
  'On a number line, ten more is one jump of +10 to the right; ten less is one jump of -10 to the left.',
  'Crossing 100 still works the same way: ten more than 97 is 107; ten less than 107 is 97.'
